    <p>
    Description Of the Application Indetail For User
    <ul>
    	<li>This is an internal organization application which is intended to provide a better medium to connect Mentor(a person who wants to share his expertise) 
    	and Mentee(a person who wants to improve his skills in that particular expertise).</li>
    	<li>This is not a performance evaluator for compensation hike and this is purely in the interest of the participants</li>
    	<li>This application is meant to show who are available as mentors and who are available as mentees and all other communication between them can be stored in the medium of their choice.</li>
    	<li> A suggested choice of medium to store all the communication between mentor and mentee can be taken as Google Drive </li>
    	</ul>
    
    <br>
    <br>
    
    Duties or Resposibilities of Mentor
   	<ul>
   		<li>Mentor can create a  program from the existing list of courses available and set the course level and group for the program</li>
   		<li>Mentor can create a program(on which he has expertise) to assist someone(mentee who wants to learn) in improving their skills in that particular area</li>
   		<li>Mentor can accept requests from mentees for the programs he created</li>
   		<li>Mentor can reject requests from the mentees</li>
   		<li>Mentor can assist a max of 4 and a minimum of 1 mentee per program</li>
   		<li>Mentor can only guide students to the material based on his expertise. There will not be any teaching sessions. Only respective links will be provided in the Mentor Notes.</li>
   		<li>Mentor can control the status of Mentee any time</li>   
   		<li>Any Notes larger in size of data will be uploaded as a document to GDrive and the link will be shared to the Mentee</li>	
   	</ul>
    
    <br>
    <br>
    
    Duties or Responsibilites of Mentee
    <ul>
    	<li>Mentee can join a program he wish to learn from the available programs provided by different Mentors</li>
    	<li>Mentee can join a program(program per mentor) only once</li>
    	<li>Mentee can send requests to the programs he is interested in </li>
    	<li>Mentee can withdraw the requests he sent when the requests are still in Waiting status</li>
    	<li>Mentee can go through the links provided by the Mentor and update his status to mentor</li>
    	<li>Mentee can send only 3 request(including waiting, rejected) to a program</li> 
    
    </ul>
    
